I stopped in for the first time ever prior to a interview for a cooks position at Philly Bros last Friday, and purchased a sandwich and a drink. The sandwich was extremely oily and wet and almost impossible to hold, though tasty.  The bread was very unimpressive bland and flattened.  As a multi decade commercial sandwich maker, I knew given some time, I could easily improve on the sandwich I had just finished only half of.  After a few mins of our first meeting, new owner Bart was insistent on me handling food right away and seemed interested in suggestions to improve the bread and make other changes to help.  The cook he put me to train with I noticed immediately handled food with bare hands clearly dirty under and around the fingernails,  and was generally in a foul mood, and difficult for me to understand. By my third shift I was getting a handle on the entire menu, but we were very slow so I decided to use my time and do some extra cleaning i could clearly see was needed and being ignored.  What I found was quite disgusting in rotten and foul vegetables and meats behind counters where food was prepped, and dirty soiled crusty dishes essential to the making of the menu were being ignored. I cleaned old meats off of a stairwell and encountered several insects during all.  I probably should have realized me verbalizing these food safety complaints, would get me in trouble. The next day, after being scheduled for the entire first shift that week, and being promised a key to open up first shift by new owner Anna, I received a text from owner Bart, firing me for being "unqualified", a odd excuse because I had made 1000's of sandwiches at far busier places with mostly outstanding reviews over a couple decades.  Lastly, the frozen beef they use for most all beef dishes, may or may not comport with the Islamic only standards advertised in the store.  Weird to be the new guy and only one to insist on wearing plastic gloves handling food which seems like a easy adjustment to make in a Covid world, but talking about it, and insisting on some cleaning standards, got me fired pretty quickly.  I would not recommend this place to anyone with the current owners in charge, they seem unqualified on food prep as fresh foods were handled with dirty hands, and menu essential utensils/dishes were ignored and or poorly washed, while expired or rotten foods languished behind prep counters ignored.

I ordered from these guys yesterday, and all I have to say is that they do an amazing job with service, quality of food and communication. I ordered from them on GrubHub and something terrible happened! GrubHub cancelled my order without my knowledge, and I was very very hungry. He apologized for a mishap that was not on his fault and I was given an extra order of tenders and the fried Oreo's with no extra cost. I will definitely order in the future and I highly recommend. As a Philly native, I was excited about ordering from here and getting someone's take on the sandwich. On Grubhub, I ordered the Thin Sliced Steak Melted Cheese Sandwich combo and asked for no onions. Sandwich came to me with mayo, lettuce, tomatoes, and mushrooms on it. I did not order the Philly Bros sandwich, which does come with the mayo, lettuce, tomatoes, and mushrooms. This establishment refused to get my order right and the lady on the phone kept telling me she is reading the sandwich and it does come with these ingredients. If I could post a pic from Grubhub to show you how you messed up an order, lost a customer, and the customer's connections. Philly Original Style vs. Philly Bros Sandwich.
